 Olalekan with some of the beneficiaries  Oyedele said he decided to save money out of his monthly allowance to buy items and donate to the school,  as part of his contributions to the society. “Some of the students lack study materials and seats. I decided to give my widow’s mite and today, I am happy to present this token,” he said. The items donated included eight chairs and desks, 100 pairs of socks, 30 exercise books, 120 writing pens and six pairs of school uniform. The state NYSC Coordinator, who was represented by Mr Amozua Abraham, called on the students to study hard, so that Oyedele’s sacrifice would not be in vain. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .